      <memberdef kind="function" id="group___standard_math_1ga20e50ab9d6b10af0e2940d9419448f42" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>int</type>
        <definition>int rand</definition>
        <argsstring>()</argsstring>
        <name>rand</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Generate a pseudo-random integer between 0 and <ref refid="group___standard_math_1ga690f251553b39fd4f31894826141b61a" kindref="member">RAND_MAX</ref> inclusive. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This function can be seeded by <ref refid="group___standard_math_1ga83a727cc697aea22e24cad5f39198dd2" kindref="member">srand()</ref>.</para>
<para>A simple way to change the range to be an integer between 0 and n-1 inclusive is using % e.g. <computeroutput><ref refid="group___standard_math_1ga20e50ab9d6b10af0e2940d9419448f42" kindref="member">rand()</ref> % n</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="return"><para>The pseudo-randomly generated number </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
